Lagos Boxing Hall of Fame (LBHF), the organisers of the Lagos Monthly Saturday Boxing Show yesterday announced its decision to not to host this month’s edition of the event.   The show, which brings together the best amateur pugilists in Lagos state, was scheduled to hold on the last Saturday of the month at the Molade Okoya-Thomas Sports Hall, Teslim Balogun Stadium, Lagos will now hold at a date later to be announced.   The coordinator for the tournament, Tajudeen Alabi, speaking to NationSports, said that the decision to not hold the premier amateur boxing event in Nigeria was to celebrate the Muslim holy month of Ramadan, which started last weekend.     Forms out in Lagos, Benin for Okpekpe 10km road     Platini, Blatter face fraud trial in June     FIFA launches streaming football service   As one of Nigeria’s longest running sporting events, the Boxing Show pulls hundreds of boxing fans from the nooks and crannies of Lagos State every last Saturday of the month as well as amateur boxers who are only too happy to showcase their skills in the ring.   He stated: “The Saturday Boxing Show which was scheduled to hold on the last Saturday of the month will not hold because of the holy month of Ramadan. This is an act of respect for our Muslim brothers and sisters as they undergo their yearly fasting.   “Moving the event to a later date will also ensure that our athletes are in top shape for the next competition in June,” he added.   The Monthly Saturday Boxing Show has been on-going since July 2009 and recently hosted its 119th edition in March.